The paper discusses a framework for coordinating task- and motion-level operations in multirobot systems, which falls under the domain of robotics (cs.RO). The framework involves using temporal networks to reason about constraints and generate plans, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and planning (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the long-term autonomy of multirobot systems, which falls under the domain of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and systems and control (cs.SY).
